					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records an agreement given by the temple servants of Tiruppāttuṟai to supply 16 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of ghee for burning a light on the day of Kārttigai in Kārttika month every year, for the 16 sheep they received from a resident of the village. This seems to be assignable to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rājēndra-Chōḷa I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
